Convolution Neural Network with Keras¶

A convolutional neural network consists of an input and an output layer, as well as multiple hidden layers. The hidden layers of a CNN typically consist of convolutional layers, RELU layer i.e. activation function, pooling layers, fully connected layers and normalization layers. 1

Convolutional

Convolutional layers apply a convolution operation to the input, passing the result to the next layer. The convolution emulates the response of an individual neuron to visual stimuli.

Each convolutional neuron processes data only for its receptive field. Although fully connected feedforward neural networks can be used to learn features as well as classify data, it is not practical to apply this architecture to images. A very high number of neurons would be necessary, even in a shallow (opposite of deep) architecture, due to the very large input sizes associated with images, where each pixel is a relevant variable. For instance, a fully connected layer for a (small) image of size 100 x 100 has 10000 weights for each neuron in the second layer. The convolution operation brings a solution to this problem as it reduces the number of free parameters, allowing the network to be deeper with fewer parameters. For instance, regardless of image size, tiling regions of size 5 x 5, each with the same shared weights, requires only 25 learnable parameters. In this way, it resolves the vanishing or exploding gradients problem in training traditional multi-layer neural networks with many layers by using backpropagation.

Pooling

Convolutional networks may include local or global pooling layers, which combine the outputs of neuron clusters at one layer into a single neuron in the next layer. For example, max pooling uses the maximum value from each of a cluster of neurons at the prior layer. Another example is average pooling, which uses the average value from each of a cluster of neurons at the prior layer.

from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Dense, Dropout, Activation, Flatten
from keras.layers import Conv2D, MaxPooling2D

#initialize Sequential neural network - inicjalizacja sieci - proste api
convNN = Sequential()
# 5x5 convolution with 2x2 stride and 32 filters - 5 warstw konwulencji
#funkcja aktywacji relu - nieliniowa
convNN.add(Conv2D(5, (5, 5), strides = (1, 1), padding='same', \
                  input_shape=(32, 32, 3), \
                  activation='relu'))
#convNN.add(Activation('relu'))

convNN.add(Conv2D(5, (3, 3), strides = (3, 3)))
convNN.add(Activation('relu'))

convNN.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(3, 3)))

convNN.add(Dropout(0.25))
#convNN.add(Conv2D(32, (3, 3), strides = (2, 2)))
#convNN.add(Activation('relu'))

#After convolution blocks we need feed-forward network to perform classyfication
convNN.add(Flatten()) ## Flatten turns 3x3x32 into 288x1

#rozmiar wejcia sieci
convNN.add(Dense(50))

#zadanie wizualne - sprawdza sie 'relu', ale do klasyfikacji moe by inna np.sigmoid, tang hiperbol.
convNN.add(Activation('relu'))

# jesli sie sie przeucza to mona dodac dropuoty
#convNN.add(Dropout(0.5))

# w wartswie wyjciowej powinno by tyle warstw ile klas do rozpatrzenia - tutaj 10 (byo wyej)
convNN.add(Dense(num_classes))

#softmax: normalizuje eby suma wyj rwna 1 - interpretacja rozkadu gstoci prawdopodob. midzy klasami 
#dodatkowe wzmocnienie (wykadnicze , nieliniowe) wyj, eby najmocniejszy si bardziej odrnia
convNN.add(Activation('softmax'))


#lepiej mie wiele warstw z mniejszymi filtrami ni jedn warstw z duym

Build convolution neural model for Minist data¶

MNIST is a simple computer vision dataset. It consists of images of handwritten digits like these: The MNIST database has a training set of 60,000 examples, and a test set of 10,000 examples.

Train convolution neural network for MNIST, evaluate the learning process by plotting the loss fitand evaluation loss change.

What affection has convolution on training process and on number of weights?

In [8]:
#Build convolution neural model for Minist data, remember to adjust input shape
# wykonane na podstawie zaj laboratoryjnych oraz ksiki "Uczenie maszynowe w Pythonie"-O'REILLY-Chris Albon


import numpy as np
from keras.datasets import mnist
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Dense, Dropout, Flatten
from keras.layers.convolutional import Conv2D, MaxPooling2D
from keras.utils import np_utils
from keras import backend as K

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#wczytanie danych i wywietlenie ich ksztatu

(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = mnist.load_data()

print('Train dataset:', x_train.shape)
print('Test dataset:', x_test.shape)

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#wyplotowanie przykadowych liczb

%matplotlib inline
plt.figure(figsize=(1,1))
image_id1=59999
plt.imshow(x_train[image_id1])
plt.axis('off')
print('-target number1: ', y_train[image_id1])

plt.figure(figsize=(1,1))
image_id2=1
plt.imshow(x_train[image_id2])
plt.axis('off')
print('-target number2: ', y_train[image_id2])
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#HINT
#Loaded data are in shape (m,w,h) where: m-number of examples, w-width, h-height
#Keras expect data to be in shape (m,w,h,c) where: c-number of channels. => RESHAPE needed

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#zdefiniowanie informacji o obrazie
channels = 1               #obrazek czarno-biay => gboko(intensywno piksela)=1 obraz jest matryc, jeli kolorowy to RGB-mapa cech.
height = x_train.shape[1]  #wynika z danych = 28 
width = x_train.shape[2]   #wynika z danych = 28

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Przeksztacenie danych uczcych i testowych na cechy
x_train=x_train.reshape(x_train.shape[0],width,height,channels)
x_test=x_test.reshape(x_test.shape[0],width,height,channels)

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#zastosowanie one-hot kodowania dla wektora docelowego
y_train = np_utils.to_categorical(y_train)
y_test = np_utils.to_categorical(y_test)


#okrelenie liczby klas
num_classes = y_test.shape[1]

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#normalizacja - zmiana skali intensywnoci piksela na wartoci w przedziale 0-1
x_train_normalized = x_train.astype('float32')
x_test_normalized = x_test.astype('float32')

x_train_normalized = x_train / 255   #podzielenie przez max wartosc
x_test_normalized = x_test / 255     #podzielenie przez max wartosc

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#inicjalizacja sieci neuronowej
network=Sequential()

#Dodanie warstwy splotowej: 
network.add(Conv2D(filters=64, kernel_size=(5,5), input_shape=(width,height,channels), activation='relu'))


#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#dodanie warstwy buforowej z oknem 2x2
network.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

#dodanie dropout - eby sie nie przeuczy
network.add(Dropout(0.5))

#dodanie spaszczenia do danych wejciowych
network.add(Flatten())

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#dodanie w peni poczonej warstwy 128 jednostek z funkcj aktywacji relu
network.add(Dense(128, activation='relu'))

#dodanie dropout - eby sie nie przeuczy
network.add(Dropout(0.5))

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#dodanie w peni poczonej warstwy z funkcj aktywacji softmax
# w wartswie wyjciowej powinno by tyle warstw ile klas do rozpatrzenia

network.add(Dense(num_classes,activation="softmax"))

#softmax: normalizuje eby suma wyj rwna 1 - interpretacja rozkadu gstoci prawdopodob. midzy klasami 
#dodatkowe wzmocnienie (wykadnicze , nieliniowe) wyj, eby najmocniejszy si bardziej odrnia
#network.add(Activation('softmax'))

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#AUGUMENTACJA TUTAJ SZKODZI !!! - duo lepsza dokadno bez przeksztace obrazw :<

# datagen = ImageDataGenerator(

# datagen.fit(x_train_normalized)
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

#kompilacja sieci neuronowej : zdefiniowanie dokadnoci jakowspczynnika wydajnoci

#wybr optymalizatora
#alogorytm gradiendu prostego ze wspczynnikiem uczenia 0.05
#optimizer = keras.optimizers.sgd(lr=0.05)

network.compile(loss='categorical_crossentropy', optimizer="rmsprop", metrics=['accuracy'])

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#wytrenowanie sieci neuronowej
run_hist_rmsprop = network.fit(x_train_normalized,  #cechy
                               y_train,             #wektor docelowy
                               batch_size=1000,     #rozmiar minigrupy - 1000 prbek - liczba obserwacji w zbiorze
                               epochs=10,           #liczba epok
                               validation_data=(x_test_normalized, y_test), #dane do oceny
                               shuffle=True,        #przemieszanie danych po kadej epoce 
                               verbose=1)           #verbose = 0: no verbose; 1: progress barr; 2: summary afer epch
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

from keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator

datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    # set input mean to 0 over the dataset
    featurewise_center=False,
    # set each sample mean to 0
    samplewise_center=False,
    # divide inputs by std of dataset
    featurewise_std_normalization=False,
    # divide each input by its std
    samplewise_std_normalization=False,
    # apply ZCA whitening
    zca_whitening=False,
    zca_epsilon=0.00001,
    # randomly rotate images in the range (deg 0 to 180)
    rotation_range=0,
    # randomly shift images horizontally
    width_shift_range=0.1,
    # randomly shift images vertically
    height_shift_range=0.1,
    # randomly flip images
    horizontal_flip=False,
    # randomly flip images
    vertical_flip=False)

datagen.fit(x_train)

ImageDataGenerator also allows to read data from disk¶

train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
rescale = 1./255,
horizontal_flip = True,
fill_mode = "nearest",
zoom_range = 0.3,
width_shift_range = 0.3,
height_shift_range=0.3,
rotation_range=30)

test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
rescale = 1./255,
horizontal_flip = True,
fill_mode = "nearest",
zoom_range = 0.3,
width_shift_range = 0.3,
height_shift_range=0.3,
rotation_range=30)

train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(
"path/to/train/data",
target_size = (img_height, img_width),
batch_size = batch_size, 
class_mode = "categorical")

validation_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_directory(
'path/to/validation/data',
target_size = (img_height, img_width),
class_mode = "categorical")
